Q: Update ChatMessageContent value in Semantic Kernel response A: <p>If you prefer the chat history to reflect only what the user sees, you can replace the last assistant message with a new <code>ChatMessageContent</code> containing the rephrased text and add detailed metadata to preserve provenance. SK’s <code>ChatHistory</code> currently exposes <code>AddMessage</code> APIs. If you’re maintaining your own list or wrapper, implement a “replace last assistant message” operation.</p>
<p>This way the History matches what the user saw and Metadata keeps provenance (original vs. rephrased). But please dont keep original ModelId with modified content. This causes inconsistency. Analytics and Audits will be completely misleading.</p>
<pre><code>ChatMessageContent original = await _chatCompletionService.GetChatMessageContentAsync(
    chatHistory, execSettings, kernel);

ChatMessageContent rephrased = await _rephraseService.GetChatMessageContentAsync(
    new ChatHistory().AddUserMessage(original.Content!), rephraseSettings, kernel);

var replaced = new ChatMessageContent(
    role: AuthorRole.Assistant,
    content: rephrased.Content,
    authorName: original.AuthorName,
    modelId: rephrased.ModelId ?? &quot;post-processed&quot;,
    innerContent: rephrased.InnerContent,
    metadata: new()
    {
        [&quot;postProcessed&quot;] = true,
        [&quot;postProcessKind&quot;] = &quot;rephrase&quot;,
        [&quot;originalModelId&quot;] = original.ModelId,
        [&quot;originalContent&quot;] = original.Content,
        [&quot;originalInnerContent&quot;] = original.InnerContent,
        [&quot;rephraseModelId&quot;] = rephrased.ModelId,
    }
);

// Replace last assistant message in your history (pseudo-code)
chatHistory.RemoveLastAssistantMessage();
chatHistory.AddMessage(replaced);

return replaced;
</code></pre>
<p>If you want to make it more ergonomic then encapsulate the metadata convention in one place:</p>
<pre><code>public static ChatMessageContent BuildPostProcessed(
    ChatMessageContent original,
    ChatMessageContent rephrased,
    string kind = &quot;rephrase&quot;)
{
    return new ChatMessageContent(
        role: AuthorRole.Assistant,
        content: rephrased.Content,
        authorName: original.AuthorName,
        modelId: rephrased.ModelId ?? &quot;post-processed&quot;,
        innerContent: rephrased.InnerContent,
        metadata: new()
        {
            [&quot;postProcessed&quot;] = true,
            [&quot;postProcessKind&quot;] = kind,
            [&quot;originalModelId&quot;] = original.ModelId,
            [&quot;originalContent&quot;] = original.Content,
            [&quot;rephraseModelId&quot;] = rephrased.ModelId,
        }
    );
}
</code></pre>
<p>Just to answer blatantly on your question: You have to decide whether to append it or replace the last assistant message. In both cases, keep provenance in <code>Metadata</code> . Hope it helps you</p>

Q: Visual Studio Code C++ Build finished with error(s) A: <p>I was also facing the same issue from last two days. I have multiple time reinstalled the msys64, VS code but outcome was still same. I have also watch multiple tutorial for this but nothing changes.</p>
<p>Then I open my msys64 and try to find my g++.exe then I found it in ucrt64 instead of mingw64. Then I changed the path, also my tasks.json.</p>
<pre><code>
{
    &quot;version&quot;: &quot;2.0.0&quot;,
    &quot;tasks&quot;: [
        {
            &quot;type&quot;: &quot;cppbuild&quot;,
            &quot;label&quot;: &quot;C/C++: g++.exe build active file&quot;,
            &quot;command&quot;: &quot;C:\\msys64\\ucrt64\\bin\\g++.exe&quot;,
            &quot;args&quot;: [
                &quot;-fdiagnostics-color=always&quot;,
                &quot;-g3&quot;,
                &quot;-Wall&quot;,
                &quot;${file}&quot;,
                &quot;-o&quot;,
                &quot;${fileDirname}\\${fileBasenameNoExtension}.exe&quot;
            ],
            &quot;options&quot;: {
                // &quot;${fileDirname}&quot; also gives the same problem.
                &quot;cwd&quot;: &quot;C:\\msys64\\ucrt64\\bin&quot;
            },
            &quot;problemMatcher&quot;: [
                &quot;$gcc&quot;
            ],
            &quot;group&quot;: {
                &quot;kind&quot;: &quot;build&quot;,
            },
            &quot;detail&quot;: &quot;compiler: C:\\msys64\\ucrt64\\bin\\g++.exe&quot;
        },
        {
            &quot;type&quot;: &quot;shell&quot;,
            &quot;label&quot;: &quot;Run C/C++: g++.exe&quot;,
            &quot;command&quot;: &quot;C:\\msys64\\ucrt64\\bin\\g++.exe -g3 -Wall \&quot;${file}\&quot; -o \&quot;${fileDirname}\\${fileBasenameNoExtension}.exe\&quot;&quot;,
            &quot;options&quot;: {
                &quot;cwd&quot;: &quot;C:\\msys64\\ucrt64\\bin&quot;
            },
            &quot;problemMatcher&quot;: [
                &quot;$gcc&quot;
            ],
            &quot;detail&quot;: &quot;compiler: C:\\msys64\\ucrt64\\bin\\g++.exe&quot;
        }
    ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>And last don't forget to save the json file 👍.</p>

